    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "mummichog requires two lists of m/z features, the significant list (e.g. selected by univariate statistics) and the reference list (all features detected in the MS experiment)... mummichog computes all possibly matched metabolites, and searches the reference metabolic network for all the modules that can be formed by these tentative metabolites... The algorithms were experimentally validated on the activation of innate immune cells.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes 'mummichog' (lowercase), not 'Mummichog 3'. The version number '3' is not mentioned anywhere in the paper. The core functionality (feature table input, network mapping without upfront identification) is accurate and well-supported.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1003123",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "How does Mummichog 3 accept untargeted metabolomics feature tables as input and predict functional activity by mapping features onto metabolic networks without requiring metabolite identification?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T06:20:30.039680+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": null,
      "asbval:note": "No mention of Python as the implementation language in any passage. The paper states 'The mummichog software is available at http://atcg.googlecode.com' but does not specify the programming language used.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1003123",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "no",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Python",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0007675"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T06:20:30.039680+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000340"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "In return, the predicted metabolites in these significant modules (and similarly for pathways) are more likely to be true, and they form the 'activity network' for this particular experiment... Mummichog collects these metabolites, and look up all their isotopic derivatives and adducts in [reference list]. A confidence rating system is applied to filter for qualified metabolites... All the qualified metabolites carry over their connections in the reference metabolic network, and form the 'activity network' for this specific experiment.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly describes output as activity networks mapping predicted metabolites to modules and pathways, with statistical significance reporting.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1003123",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Functional activity prediction report mapping features to metabolic network modules and pathways",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T06:20:30.039680+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "We present a set of computational algorithms which, by leveraging the collective power of metabolic pathways and networks, predict functional activity directly from spectral feature tables without a priori identification of metabolites.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes the mummichog pipeline and algorithms, but does not use version designation 'Mummichog 3'. The paper is from 2013 and refers to the tool simply as 'mummichog'.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1003123",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "title_concept",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Reconstruct the metabolic network-based feature-table analysis pipeline in Mummichog 3",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-16T06:20:30.039680+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The candidate card references 'Mummichog 3' but the paper describes 'mummichog' without version number. This appears to be a version conflation by the extractor.",
        "The card claims Python as a tool, but the paper provides no information about implementation language. This may be an assumption by the extractor not grounded in the paper.",
        "The research question accurately captures the core methodology but adds a version number not present in the source material."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 3,
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
