    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/metabolomics-functional-prediction-workflow-validation/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "The software implementation of our approach is named mummichog (mummichog is an American Indian term for by groups, also name of a small fish which live by groups).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes mummichog (version not specified, likely v1 from 2013) and its core workflows on metabolomics datasets. The card claims validation of 'Mummichog 3' migration to a new GitHub organization. The paper does not discuss version 3, GitHub migration, organizational standards, or CI/CD workflows\u2014these are modern software engineering concerns not addressed in the 2013 paper. The paper validates mummichog's functional prediction on real metabolomics data (moDC, urine, yeast), which aligns with the 'executes core workflows correctly' aspect, but the migration/organizational context is entirely absent from the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1371-journal-pcbi-1003123",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "metabolomics-functional-prediction-workflow-validation",
